result.execSummary:
The defendant Donzel L Morse was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Per Order of Presiding Judge, Felony Division, this request/motion is hereby assigned to the Hon. Dennis R. Cimpl, Br. 19, for review. jbs
Letter from DOC seeking review of probationary term in count two.

Defendant Donzel L Morse in court with attorney Eric Daniel Lowenberg.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  As to both counts:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, elements and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. Court orders defendant provide a DNA sample.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.
As to Count 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  1 YEAR at the House of Corrections  CONCURRENT to Count 2 and consecutive to any other sentence.  The  first 5 months to be served straight and 7 months at the Day Reporting Center.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 3 YEARS probation.
As to Count 2: The Court sentence the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS at the House of Corrections first 5 months to be served straight and 1 month at the Day Reporting Center.
Court orders a total of 2 days credit
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 2 YEARS probation.

Conditions of Probation:
- No further violations rising to the level of probable cause
- Cooperate with the Probation Department
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any treatment programs deemed necessary
- No possession of alcohol or illegal drugs; no possession of drug paraphernalia
- Random urine screens
- Seek and maintain full-time employment and/or school
- Obtain a GED/HSED
- no contact with Karen M
- participate in the Oh Yeah program
- Provide a DNA sample.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $500.00 to Karen M and $3300.00 to WEA Trust Member Benefit, joint and several with 15CF780
Pay DNA surcharges;
All court costs and applicable fees of supervision.
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter
